..TEXT:
|quei ch'ancor fa li padri ai figli scarsi~: The
example of Pha,ethon still makes fathers cautious in granting
their sons' requests because of the tragedy that resulted when
Pha,ethon was allowed by his father to drive the chariot of the
Sun.  See Ovid, ^Metam.~ II, 31-328.
