..TEXT:
|tetragono~: "Foursquare," presenting upon every
side a bold front or a show of unyielding resistance.  See
Aristotle, ^Eth. Nicom.~ I, 10, 1100b,
"%tau%epsilon%tau%rho%$alpha%gamma%omega%nu%o%varsigma\"
("tetragonus"), and ^Rhet.~ III, 11, 1411b.  |ventura~: See
^Inf.~ II, 61 and the corresponding note.  Also see ^Inf.~ XV,
91-93.
