..TEXT:
|Da indi~: From the |cospetto etterno~, vs. 39.
|Da~ may be considered redundant here.  |s@i come~... |organo~:
Since the prophecies of what is to come are dire indeed for
Dante, one may wonder at the comparison with ^sweet~ music.  But
Cacciaguida is one of the blessed and in God's will is his peace
(^Par.~ III, 85), that is, all things willed by God or allowed
by God, such as these "contingent things," are "sweet."
