..TEXT:
|la compagnia malvagia e scempia~: The other
Florentine exiles of the party of the Bianchi.  Of Dante's
movements for some years after his exile, little is known for
certain.  In 1302 he was at San Godenzo in the Mugello at a
meeting of the Bianchi and the next year at Forl@i, where he
served at one point as an aide to Scarpetta degli Ordelaffi.  On
July 20, 1304, the exiled Bianchi made an abortive attempt to
effect an entry into the city, but from this attempt Dante seems
to have held aloof, and about this time he separated himself from
the Bianchi, having come to hold them in the bitter disesteem
which the adjectives here reflect.
