..TEXT:
|lo monte~... |levaro~: Purgatory, from the
summit of which (beautiful because of the Garden of Eden there)
the pilgrim is said to have been lifted by the eyes of Beatrice.
Such turns of phrase should not be overlooked, for they are
always clear pointers to the allegorical role of Beatrice, as the
second of three lights.  See C. S. Singleton (1958), pp. 23-31.
|levaro~ = ^levarono.~
