..TEXT:
|quel che~... |agrume~: Dante has seen things
-- particularly in Hell, where he has seen the damned and where
they are punished there -- which, if reported, are going to prove
very sour to some of his readers, who might otherwise offer him
hospitality in his exile.  Shall he make a true report, or shall
he withhold certain things?  |agrume~: "Sourness."
